cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB

This paper describes methods and systems for generating entity embeddings for use with machine learning models. Entity embeddings are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) tasks, which fall under the categories of cs.CL and cs.IR, respectively. However, the paper also discusses benchmarking tasks and the sharing of embeddings among multiple machine learning models, which are more closely related to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of a feature registry for storing features associated with entities suggests a potential connection to databases (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely categories for this paper are cs.LG and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.DB.
